      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera represents the pinnacle of the analog driving experience, featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis retains its telepathic feedback thanks to the factory hydraulic steering rack and a well-sorted multi-link rear suspension geometry. Critically, this example has undergone a proactive IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal (RMS) replacement, addressing the primary mechanical concerns of the M96 architecture. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the mechanical synchronization between the throttle bodies and the exhaust note remains flawless, offering a visceral performance profile that modern GTs lack.",
